Locally Differentially Private Protocols for mean estimation
- this project contains implementations of several LDP mechanisms
  including Improved Laplace Mechanism, Piecewise Mechanism, and Hybrid Mechanism
- each mechanism is implemented in its own Python file
- each file includes functions for loading data from CSV files, applying the LDP mechanism, and
  evaluating the results
- the code uses standard libraries such as numpy and pandas for data manipulation
- command-line interfaces are provided for easy execution and parameter tuning
// Public dataset used for interim report:Cortez, P., Cerdeira, A., Almeida, F., Matos, T., & Reis, J. (2009). Wine Quality [Dataset]. UCI Machine Learning Repository. 
  https://doi.org/10.24432/C56S3T.
  - Incase the link is not accessible, the dataset can be found by searching for "UCI Wine Quality Dataset" online.//
- Public dataset for final report:	A. Hussain, “Amazon_Sales_Dataset,” Kaggle.com, 2025. https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/aliiihussain/amazon-sales-dataset/discussion?sort=hotness
 
